dc_title_s: LiDAR-Derived Countywide 1.5m Hillshade Image for Sheboygan County, WI 2004
dc_description_s: This data represents a LiDAR-derived countywide hillshade image forSheboygan County, Wisconsin in 2004. The coordinate system is WTM (EPSG 3071). Hillshading is a technique used to visualize terrain as shaded relief, illuminating it with a hypothetical light source. The illumination value for each raster cell is determined by its orientation to the light source, which is based on slope and aspect.
dc_creator_sm: Wisconsin Department of Administration - Geographic Information Office
